---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Local SEO for Small Businesses: Practical Guide | visibilite-locale.online"
  description="Local SEO strategy tailored for small and local businesses. Attract customers in your area through Google search."
  lang="en"
  ogImage="/images/guide/en-businesses.webp"

>
  <section class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <nav class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/en/guide-seo-local" class="hover:text-blue-600">Local SEO Guide</a> &rsaquo;
        <span class="text-gray-900">Businesses</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Local SEO for Businesses</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Strategies tailored for shops, restaurants, and tradespeople to dominate local search.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- Image hero -->
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-8">
    <img
      src="/images/guide/en-businesses.webp"
      alt=""
      class="w-full rounded-xl object-cover shadow-sm"
      loading="eager"
      width="1200"
      height="400"
      style="max-height:320px"
      onerror="this.style.display='none'"
    />
  </div>


  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 prose">
      <h2>Local SEO for restaurants</h2>
      <p>
        Restaurants are among the most locally searched businesses. Your Google Business Profile listing must include the menu, food photos, precise hours, and options (patio, delivery, reservations).
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Add your menu directly to your GBP listing</li>
        <li>Post professional food photos regularly</li>
        <li>Indicate available services: delivery, takeout, dine-in</li>
        <li>Respond to every review, especially negative ones</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Local SEO for retail shops</h2>
      <p>
        For retail businesses, local visibility means highlighting your products, hours, and location. Use GBP attributes specific to your type of business.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Enable in-store inventory if you sell products</li>
        <li>Keep business hours up to date including holidays</li>
        <li>Post offers and promotions via Google Posts</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Local SEO for tradespeople</h2>
      <p>
        Tradespeople (plumbers, electricians, carpenters) often have a service area rather than a storefront. Configure your service area in GBP and create service pages by city.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Define your service area in Google Business Profile</li>
        <li>Create a page for each city or area you serve</li>
        <li>Collect reviews mentioning the city of service</li>
        <li>Add geo-tagged photos of completed work</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common mistakes businesses make</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Not updating special hours</li>
        <li>Ignoring negative reviews</li>
        <li>Having a non-mobile-friendly website</li>
        <li>Neglecting business photos</li>
        <li>Not claiming their Google Business Profile listing</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Related articles</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 text-blue-700">
          <li><a href="/en/blog/en-seo-local-restaurants/">Local SEO for Restaurants</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
